# kopah-bagit configuration
#
# Credential sources are checked in this order:
#   1. $S3CMD_CONFIG (if set)
#   2. ~/.s3cfg     (s3cmd's own default — used when $S3CMD_CONFIG is unset)
#   3. KOPAH_* env vars (below)
# This mirrors s3cmd's own resolution semantics. If none is configured,
# kopah-bagit exits non-zero with a message naming each option.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Option A — s3cmd config (recommended): if you already have ~/.s3cfg set up
# to talk to Kopah, kopah-bagit will pick it up automatically — nothing to
# configure here. To point at a non-default file, uncomment:
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# S3CMD_CONFIG=/Users/you/.s3cfg-kopah

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Option B (direct env vars, useful for CI / containers without an s3cmd
# config file):
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# KOPAH_ACCESS_KEY=...
# KOPAH_SECRET_KEY=...
# KOPAH_ENDPOINT=https://s3.kopah.uw.edu
